    <thetext>I&apos;ve tried to make the context accessible using getData/setData on the cnf viewer, but wasn&apos;t successful with this approach (required to establish new dependencies between mylyn plugins).

What works, however, is to extend the ContextTasksAdapterFactory to adapt the TaskEditorInput to the corresponding IInteractionContext (https://git.eclipse.org/r/7212).

Actions may than query the context like this:

&lt;code&gt;
IEditorPart activeEditor = PlatformUI.getWorkbench()
				.getActiveWorkbenchWindow()
				.getActivePage()
				.getActiveEditor();
Object context = ativeEditor.getEditorInput().getAdapter(IInteractionContext.class);
&lt;/code&gt;</thetext>
